  "description": "IRS Code 560 indicates additional liability is pending. Learn what this freeze typically means, how it interacts with codes 570, 971, and 290, and what to verify before advising clients.",
  "content": "<nav class=\"text-sm text-slate-400\">\n    <ol class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2\">\n      <li><a class=\"hover:text-white transition\" href=\"/\">Home</a></li>\n      <li class=\"text-slate-600\">/</li>\n      <li><a class=\"hover:text-white transition\" href=\"/resources/transcript-types/\">Resources</a></li>\n      <li class=\"text-slate-600\">/</li>\n      <li class=\"text-slate-200\">IRS Code 560 Meaning</li>\n    </ol>\n   </nav>\n\n   <header class=\"mt-6\">\n    <div class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full tm-kbd px-4 py-2 text-xs text-slate-300\">\n      <span class=\"font-semibold text-white\">IRS Transcript Codes</span> <span class=\"text-slate-500\">•</span> <span>Built for 750,000+ U.S. Tax Professionals</span>\n    </div>\n    <h1 class=\"mt-4 text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl\">IRS Code <span class=\"text-purple-300\">560</span> Meaning</h1>\n    <p class=\"mt-3 max-w-3xl text-base text-slate-300 tm-prose\">IRS Code 560 generally indicates <strong>additional liability is pending</strong>. It reflects a freeze or hold while the IRS considers assessing more tax or adjusting the module. Understanding what triggered it is key before advising clients.</p>\n    <div class=\"mt-6 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:items-center\">\n      <button type=\"button\" data-open-sample class=\"inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-purple-500 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-950 hover:bg-purple-400 transition\">View sample report</button>\n      <a href=\"/#how-it-works\" class=\"inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl tm-soft px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:border-slate-400/30 transition\">Try the parser (requires credits)</a>\n    </div>\n   </header>\n\n   <section class=\"mt-10 grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3\">\n    <article class=\"lg:col-span-2 tm-card rounded-2xl p-6 sm:p-8\">\n     <div class=\"tm-prose\">\n      <h2 class=\"text-xl font-bold text-white\">What is IRS Code 560?</h2>\n      <p class=\"mt-3 text-slate-300\"><strong>Plain-English definition:</strong> Code 560 signals that <strong>additional tax liability is pending review or assessment</strong>. It commonly appears before a formal assessment entry posts.</p>\n\n      <dl class=\"mt-5 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2\">\n        <div class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\"><dt class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-slate-300\">Common transcript type</dt><dd class=\"mt-1 text-sm text-white\">Account Transcript</dd></div>\n        <div class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\"><dt class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-slate-300\">Often appears near</dt><dd class=\"mt-1 text-sm text-white\">Codes 290, 570</dd></div>\n        <div class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\"><dt class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-slate-300\">Typical context</dt><dd class=\"mt-1 text-sm text-white\">Potential assessment adjustment</dd></div>\n        <div class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\"><dt class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-slate-300\">Client-friendly summary</dt><dd class=\"mt-1 text-sm text-white\">\"The IRS may be adding more tax\"</dd></div>\n      </dl>\n\n      <h2 class=\"mt-10 text-xl font-bold text-white\">When does Code 560 appear?</h2>\n      <ul class=\"mt-3 list-disc pl-5 text-slate-300\">\n        <li><strong>Before an assessment posts:</strong> Often precedes Code 290.</li>\n        <li><strong>During review or examination:</strong> May relate to pending adjustments.</li>\n        <li><strong>When liability changes are being evaluated:</strong> Signals the module is under review.</li>\n      </ul>\n\n      <h2 class=\"mt-10 text-xl font-bold text-white\">What should you verify?</h2>\n      <ol class=\"mt-3 list-decimal pl-5 text-slate-300 space-y-2\">\n        <li>Look for a subsequent <strong>Code 290</strong> assessment.</li>\n        <li>Check for <strong>Code 570</strong> indicating additional freeze activity.</li>\n        <li>Review <strong>Code 971</strong> for notice issuance explaining the change.</li>\n      </ol>\n\n      <hr class=\"my-10 border-slate-800/60\">\n\n      <h2 id=\"example\" class=\"text-xl font-bold text-white\">Example in a parsed report</h2>\n      <div class=\"code-block mt-5\">\n        <div class=\"code-label\">Assessment sequence</div>\n        <div class=\"space-y-3 text-sm\">\n          <div><span class=\"code-key\">Code 560</span> – <span class=\"text-slate-400\">Additional liability pending</span></div>\n          <div><span class=\"code-key\">Code 290</span> – <span class=\"text-slate-400\">Additional tax assessed</span></div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <hr class=\"my-10 border-slate-800/60\">\n\n      <h2 class=\"text-xl font-bold text-white\">FAQ</h2>\n      <div class=\"mt-4 space-y-4\">\n        <details class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\"><summary class=\"cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-white\">What does IRS Code 560 mean?</summary><p class=\"mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300\">It indicates potential additional tax liability is pending review.</p></details>\n        <details class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\"><summary class=\"cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-white\">Is Code 560 serious?</summary><p class=\"mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300\">It requires attention, as it may precede additional tax assessment.</p></details>\n        <details class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\"><summary class=\"cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-white\">Does 560 mean I owe more tax?</summary><p class=\"mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300\">Not necessarily yet, but it often precedes a formal assessment.</p></details>\n        <details class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\"><summary class=\"cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-white\">What other codes matter?</summary><p class=\"mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300\">Review 290, 570, and 971 for full context.</p></details>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </article>\n\n    <aside class=\"space-y-6\">\n      <div class=\"tm-card rounded-2xl p-6\">\n        <h2 class=\"text-base font-bold text-white